      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 94: The buffering still does not reliably cover the race this patch is trying to fix. Because `observe(on: MainScheduler.instance)` is applied before the subscription closure, an auth event emitted while `addDevice()` is running is queued to the main scheduler and the closure may not execute until after `operationId` has already been assigned. In that case it skips the buffer path and handles the result directly, which is fine for matching op ids, but the explicit drain of `pendingAuthResults` is not a reliable replay mechanism and state mutation is split across scheduler timing. Move the operation-id/buffering decision before `observe(on:)`, or serialize `operationId` assignment and event processing on one queue/actor so the decision is made in emission order.",
      "revId": "5f2ab29ba7be7d1bed1d9b031a5df613fe4cd8dd",
